KZN premier Willies Mchunu and the South African consul in Shanghai Thabo Thage have lined up a series of meetings for the KZN delegation attending the Global Conference on Health Promotion and Mayors Forum in Shanghai.The premier, who is accompanied by MEC for health Dr Sibongiseni Dhlomo and eThekwini mayor Zandile Gumede, will engage with potential investors from the municipality of Shanghai and province of Guangzhou to consolidate programmes aimed at implementing Memorandums of Understanding signed with KwaZulu-Natal. We have brought warm greetings from the people of KwaZulu-Natal, Mchunu told his hosts. We are here to tell of our desire to be part of the global community. We believe that we cannot prosper in isolation. We want to state unequivocally that we are determined to take advantage of opportunities offered by being part of Brics, an organisation established to safeguard the interests of the so-called developing nations. The premier said his administration was doubling its efforts to ensure that the people of KwaZulu-Natal benefit from Brics. Our commitment is informed by the dedication of our leadership starting from the president of the Republic of South Africa JG Zuma and the president of the Peoples Republic of China, Xi Jinping, Mchunu said. Both presidents have worked hard to ensure that the bond between the peoples of China and South Africa remain strong. TNA REPORTER